Global Ball Screw for Injection Molding Machines Market Insights
Ball Screw for Injection Molding Machines Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Ball Screw for Injection Molding Machines Market Overview
The Ball Screw for Injection Molding Machines market has witnessed significant growth, with a market value reaching approximately USD 2.5 billion in 2024 and projected to grow at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2025 to 2030. Ball screws are integral components used to provide precise motion control in injection molding machines, supporting industries such as automotive, consumer goods, and packaging. The increasing demand for high-precision and automated manufacturing processes is driving the adoption of ball screws. As industries shift towards more sustainable and efficient operations, the demand for these components continues to rise, contributing to the overall market expansion.

